==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Concertina
<hw>Con`cer*ti"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From It.
<ets>concerto</ets> a concert.]</ety> <def>A small musical instrument on
the principle of the accordion. It is a small elastic box, or bellows,
having free reeds on the inside, and keys and handles on the outside of
each of the two hexagonal heads.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concertino</ent>⟦br⟧
